{% block content %}
<section class="wy-body">
    <h1 class="wy-body__title" style="color:#f53617">How to Find Us</h1>
    <h2 class="wy-body__title" style="color:#f53617">Map</h2>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="http://maps.google.com/maps/api/js?sensor=false"></script><div style="overflow:hidden;height:500px;width:100%;"><div id="gmap_canvas" style="height:500px;width:100%;"><style>#gmap_canvas img{max-width:none!important;background:none!important}</style><a class="google-map-code" href="http://www.themecircle.net/wordpress-magazine/" id="get-map-data">wordpress magazine themes</a></div></div><script type="text/javascript"> function init_map(){var myOptions = {zoom:14,center:new google.maps.LatLng(52.15025499999999,-3.3989294000000427),mapTypeId: google.maps.MapTypeId.ROADMAP};map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById("gmap_canvas"), myOptions);marker = new google.maps.Marker({map: map,position: new google.maps.LatLng(52.15025499999999, -3.3989294000000427)});infowindow = new google.maps.InfoWindow({content:"<b>Wyeside Arts</b><br/>Castle Street<br/>LD2 3BN Builth Wells" });google.maps.event.addListener(marker, "click", function(){infowindow.open(map,marker);});infowindow.open(map,marker);}google.maps.event.addDomListener(window, 'load', init_map);</script>

    <hr />

    <h2 class="wy-body__title" style="color:#f53617">Parking</h2>
    <p>Unfortunately we don’t have any visitor parking, but Builth Wells’ Groe public car park is less than 200m walk away from our centre and parking is free after 6pm. The car park can be found to the west of Wyeside next to the public park which runs alongside the river Wye.</p>

    <hr />

    <h2 class="wy-body__title" style="color:#f53617">Arriving by Bus</h2>
    <p>There are many buses that travel through Builth Wells. For the latest bus information try the journey planner on the <a target="_blank" href="https://www.traveline.cymru/">Traveline Cymru website</a> or call them on 0871 200 22 33.</p>

    <hr />

    <h2 class="wy-body__title" style="color:#f53617">Arriving by Rail</h2>
    <p>The picturesque Heart of Wales line passes through Builth Road Station, which can be found 2 miles north of Builth Wells just off the A470 to Rhayader. The Heart of Wales line runs regular services  between Swansea and Shrewsbury, and is part of the national rail network. More information is  available from the Heart of Wales website or from National Rail. Please be aware that you may need  a taxi between the station and the centre, and that as Builth Road is a request stop, you will need to flag the train down if you wish to get on.</p>

    <hr />

    <img src="/img/frontend/img/how-to-find-us.jpg" alt="Wyeside Arts Centre" style="margin:1em 0;"/>
</section>
{% endblock %}
